Imo State Police Command, yesterday, declared five female secondary students missing.
   
They are, Miss Ifeyinwa Ugwu, 14, Miss Goodness Longtale, 15, Miss John Chinasa Favour, 16, Miss Miracle Oluebube, 17 and Miss Chizoba Destiny Uchechukwu, 18. Also, declared missing was one Chukwuma Emeribe ‘m’, 75, of No. 1, Welder Road, Umuagu Umuguma in Owerri West Local Council of the state.
  
The Guardian gathered that three of the missing girls are students of Akwakuma Girls Secondary School and Ikenegbu Girls Secondary School both in Owerri, the state capital. Chinasa Favour Chizoba Destiny  Uchechukwu  “One Chukwuma Emeribe ‘m’, of No. 1, Welder Road, Umuagu Umuguma in Owerri West Local Council of Imo State, fair in complexion, about 5ft tall, has no tribal marks and speaks both Igbo and English languages fluently. He left the above address on 28/01/2022 at about 1400hrs, to an unknown destination and has not returned since then.”